# Workflow guardrails

Before running commands:
- Check whether the app scaffold exists.
- In the current pre-implementation state, install/build/dev/test commands are expected not to work.
- Do not run speculative package installs.

When starting implementation:
- Start from M0 in `docs/demo-app/05-implementation-plan.md`, but adapt it to Express + Sequelize + MySQL + external SSO.
- Confirm the desired repo layout before scaffolding if the user has not already decided:
  - monorepo: `apps/frontend`, `apps/backend`, `packages/shared-types`
  - or separate deploy-oriented frontend/backend structure

When changing docs:
- Keep `wedding-planner-deployment.md` authoritative for deployment and stack.
- Fix stale README or implementation-plan references only when the task includes documentation cleanup or when the stale text directly blocks the current change.
- Do not silently mix old and new stack decisions.

When implementing features:
- Keep changes milestone-oriented.
- Prefer end-to-end vertical slices.
- Avoid backend-only or frontend-only "done" states for milestone completion.
- Add open questions to the relevant doc when product scope is ambiguous.
